<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>After following the "<a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.loader.pluginloader.html#zend.loader.pluginloader.performance.example">Using the PluginLoader class file include cache</a>" example, I've noticed that there is inconsistent directory separators used within the generated "include file" cache script, for example</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
&lt;?php
// data/pluginLoaderCache.php
include_once 'Zend/Filter/Word\CamelCaseToDash.php';
include_once 'Zend/Filter/StringToLower.php';
</code></pre>

<p>I'm sure this is due to the fact that I'm developing on a Windows host however I can't see why only some entries are using the backslash. This will also cause issues if I deploy this file to a Linux host.</p>

